Omron to Buy Chinese Maker of Smart-Grid Components, Nikkei Says

-- B y   C h i s a k i   W a t a n a b e
-- 
2011-09-09T02:50:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-09/omron-to-buy-chinese-maker-of-smart-grid-components-nikkei-says.html
Omron Corp. (6645)  will buy all the shares
in Shanghai Best Electric Appliance Manufacturing Co. from its
founders for an estimated “a few billion yen,” the Nikkei
 reported , without saying where it got the information.  Omron, a Japanese maker of electric parts, plans to turn
the Chinese maker of smart-grid components into a wholly owned
unit as soon as the end of October once it gets approval from
Chinese authorities, the news paper reported.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Chisaki Watanabe in Tokyo at 
 cwatanabe5@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
